# SSH allowed signers for local git commit/tag verification.
# Pointed at by gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile in the `signing` fragment, so both
# the human gitconfig and the Claude agent gitconfig (claude-agent-<role>,
# which [include]s ~/.gitconfig) inherit it. See ADR 0034.
#
# This is a LOCAL trust set only: it lets `git log --show-signature` and
# `git verify-commit` confirm a commit was signed by a key listed here. It has
# no effect on signing, on GitHub's Verified badge, or on enforcement (git
# never blocks anything based on this file).
#
# Format: <principal-email> <keytype> <key-blob>
# A principal not listed here verifies as "Could not verify signature" (valid
# bytes, untrusted identity), NOT a bad/forged signature. Public keys are safe
# to commit. Append work-role identities here when that role is set up.

